Nftables is the modern Linux firewall framework that replaces the older iptables, ip6tables, arptables, and ebtables systems.
It was introduced to make packet filtering and firewall management simpler, faster, and more efficient, using a unified tool: nft.

[+] Installation:
# sudo apt install nftables
# sudo systemctl start nftables

[+] How To Use Nftables:
# nft add rule inet traffic --filter input tcp dport {22, 80, 443} accept
# nft add rule ip filter input ip protocol vmap {tcp, jump tcp chain, udp:jump udp.chain, icmp:jump icmp-chain} 

[+] Translating IPtables to Nftables:
# iptables-translate 
# iptables-saave > iptables.dump
# iptables-restore-translate -f iptables.dump

[+] Create Table:
# sudo nft add table inet first-table
# sudo nft list tables
# sudo nft delete tables inet first-table

[+] Chains:
# nft add chain ip traffic-filter output { type filter hook output priority 0 \; policy accept\; }

[+] Basic Rules: 
# nft add rule ip filter output ip addr 1.2.3.4 drop

[+] Adding Rules:
# nft add rule ip filter ip addr [IP]/24 counter
# nft add rule ip filter input tcp dport 80 drop
# nft add rule filter input icmp type echo-request accept
# nft delete rule filter output

# sudo iptables-translate -A INPUT -s [IP] -j DROP
# sudo nft add rule inet filter input ip -s addr [IP] acept
# sudo nft add rule inet output ip addr [IP] drop

# sudo nft "add rule filter input tcp --dport {22, 80, 443} addr [IP]/24"
# sudo nft add rule inet filter input icmp type echo-request drop
